http://media.guim.co.uk/fb43475b56bfe6093a370f6eaade7aa778aa17d7/0_10_4544_5763/788.jpg\" alt=\"Human Statue of Liberty: 18,000 Officers and Men at Camp Dodge, Des Moines, Iowa, Col Wm Newman Commanding, Col Rush S Wells, Directing, c 1918. Arthur S Mole & Thomas, gelatin silver print\" width=\"788\" height=\"1000\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Human Statue of Liberty: 18,000 Officers and Men at Camp Dodge, Des Moines, Iowa, Col Wm Newman Commanding, Col Rush S Wells, Directing, c1918<br></strong><strong>Arthur S Mole &amp; Thomas, g</strong><strong>elatin silver print</strong><br><br>This image from Wagstaff’s collection is one of Arthur Mole’s ‘living photographs’, where he would stand as many as 30,000 servicemen in patriotic arrangements to represent Abraham Lincoln, the Liberty Bell, or a bald eagle</span> <span class=\"element-image__credit\">Photograph: Arthur S Mole &amp; Thomas/J Paul Getty Trust</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"1ea83df07abc46a0e8efb205c573998f13816fe1\"> <img src=\"http://media.guim.co.uk/1ea83df07abc46a0e8efb205c573998f13816fe1/29_17_6829_3304/1000.jpg\" alt=\"Perspective View of the Carriage Way in the Suspension Bridge, Niagara, c 1865. Unknown US photographer, albumen silver stereograph\" width=\"1000\" height=\"484\" class=\"gu-image\" /> <figcaption> <span class=\"element-image__caption\"><strong>Perspective View of the Carriage Way in the Suspension Bridge, Niagara, c1865<br></strong><strong>Unknown US photographer, albumen silver stereograph<br></strong><br>Wagstaff was born in 1921, and after graduating from Yale served in the army, and took part in the D-Day landings. Stereographs produce a three-dimensional illusion.</span> <span class=\"element-image__credit\">Photograph: J Paul Getty Trust</span> </figcaption> </figure>  <figure class=\"element element-image\" data-media-id=\"c6c66a1ade9dda07e405f52ab66efff75b7a5440\"> <